President Obama has announced that he will be donating a portion of his $1.4 million Nobel peace prize award to various charities. The organizations that will receive donations include Fisher House, the Clinton-Bush Haiti Fund, College Summit, the Posse Foundation, the United Negro College Fund, the Hispanic Scholarship Fund, the Appalachian Leadership and Education Foundation, the American Indian College Fund, AfriCare, and the Central Asia Institute. These organizations work in areas such as providing housing for families of patients, supporting college enrollment, offering scholarships, promoting education and literacy, and addressing needs in health, agriculture, and water resource development in Africa and Central Asia.